Rating my recent empties 🎀

☁️ Bioderma Sebium H2O: After reading many reviews I decided to try this one. This is a holy grail product, and you won’t regret it!

🌿 coxir Green Tea pH Clear Foam Cleanser: Gently washes away impurities and makeup from your skin. Green tea helps control oil, while centella asiatica and snail mucin protect and calm the skin.

🌻 Goodal Green Tangerine Vita C Dark Spot Care Serum: This vitamin C changed my life, and I love it so much! This is why I love Korean skincare 🫰

♟️ haruharu wonder Black Rice Hyaluronic Toner Fragrance Free: I tried this toner as a sample and then ordered a full-size bottle because of its unique ability to soothe and smooth my skin. My combination skin drinks it right up.

🌷 Loreal Paris Glycolic Bright Dark Circle Eye Serum: I have been using this for a year, and I love it. It helps reduce puffiness, and you can see results within a few days. I purchased this because it contains niacinamide and vitamins ☺️

🪻 Loreal Paris Revitalift Filler Hyaluronic Acid Serum: This is the best serum for every skin tone! I've been using it since last year, and it makes my skin shiny, smooth, hydrated, and naturally beautiful.

🎀 Miguhara Rose Collagen Glow Multi Balm: I have semi-dry under-eyes, so my makeup often cakes up. However, this keeps it flawless!

🔮 sixam glow Double Duty Cleanser and Makeup Remover: I liked the fragrance of the product, and the texture is also good. It works efficiently to remove face makeup.

🧊 The Face Shop Fresh Jeju Aloe Ice Soothing Gel: This product feels more like a cream than an aloe vera gel; however, it's very nice.

YesStyle code: RIPAPPI21 🧿
